Today's the day - happy Virtual Charter Day 2020! We're going LIVE on Facebook at 11:30AM, and we can't wait for you to join us! Follow these quick instructions to tune in and share our live post with YOUR friends, school Facebook page audience, etc.

Visit our MI Charters Facebook page around 11:30AM, when we'll go LIVE for the big program. We'll wait for about 5 minutes before getting started so everyone can tune in.
Once you find the video on our page, click the "Share" option. Either select "Share Now (Friends)" or to share to your school's Facebook page select "More Options" then "Share to a Page" and select your school's page.
Be sure to have your school swag on, and be ready to post a photo showing it off, along with a message about why you LOVE your charter school, in the comments!

GEE’s Got Talent

This Spring, any GEE students may compete in weekly competitions. We will have a different competition each week with some prizes up for grabs and bragging rights on the line. Each participant must submit pictures/videos to the following email address; gottalent@gee-edu.com please include your name, academy, and grade level.

Our panel of GEE judges will vote on the submissions and declare the winners on GEE’s Facebook page.
Some of the contests coming your way this Spring include; Trick Shot Challenge, Mascot Art Contest, Choreography Competition, Chess Tournament, Fitness Challenges, and more! #GEEgottalent See below details for Week 1:
May 11 - May 17

post_text: Good morning GTA families! Welcome back from spring break! We hope all of you stayed safe, got some rest, and enjoyed the time with your family! Parents, I will be doing a FB live at 5:00 p.m. and will be sending a phone message about our plans moving forward. As you all know, schools have been closed for the remainder of the school year. We are continuing with our e-Learning plan that we started on March 16th. By now, you all should have received a letter from Global Educational Excellence from your child's teacher. If you did not receive the letter, please reach out to your child's teacher or email me at tolbertr@gee-edu.com. We miss you guys so much! I'll see you online at 5:00 p.m.!

post_text:
Dear Parents & Guardians,

We hope you are all doing well! Tomorrow we will begin our e-learning experience online! Please remind your scholar of the importance of logging in daily to check their email, Clever, and/or Google Classroom for updates, assignments and possibly to chat with their teacher to keep the line of communication open.

Also, tomorrow morning, from 9:00 a.m.- 11:00 a.m. sharp, you may pick up your child's Chromebook and learning packet from the school. If you have any questions, please contact your child's teacher.

Thank you,

Global Tech Staff
text:
Dear Parents & Guardians,

We hope you are all doing well! Tomorrow we will begin our e-learning experience online! Please remind your scholar of the importance of logging in daily to check their email, Clever, and/or Google Classroom for updates, assignments and possibly to chat with their teacher to keep the line of communication open.

Also, tomorrow morning, from 9:00 a.m.- 11:00 a.m. sharp, you may pick up your child's Chromebook and learning packet from the school. If you have any questions, please contact your child's teacher.

Thank you,

Global Tech Staff
